{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, equity impact assessments and bias audits should become standard practice in climate-related AI applications.",
    "Targeted funding and research support for underrepresented regions, such as Africa and South America, help address systemic disparities in research output and technology access.",
    "To mitigate algorithmic bias and promote equity, we propose integrating established AI governance frameworks such as the Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development (OECD) (2019)-which emphasize fairness, transparency, accountability, and robustness-and the IEEE Ethically Aligned Design framework (Chatila et al., 2018).",
    "These provide actionable guidance for responsible AI development in climate resilience applications.",
    "Researchers and practitioners should conduct bias audits to evaluate whether AI models systematically underperform for marginalized groups, use datasets that reflect demographic and regional diversity, and incorporate participatory design practices to engage local communities in AI tool development."
  ]
}